<TD align="left"><pre>

  <strong>LOOP CONTROL STATEMENTS</strong>

	The control statements of a language specify the order in which 
computations are performed.
	In general C consider braces { and } is used to group declerations and 
statements together into compound statements or block ,so that they are 
considered as single statement.
	Functionality of  looping can be achieved in C using loop control 
 statements like 
	<a href="while.html" target="_self"><strong>While</strong></a>
	<a href="dowhile.html" target="_self"><strong>Do While</strong></a>
	<a href="for.html" target="_self"><strong>For</strong></a>

